Definition: moral perversion
Example: impairment of virtue and moral principles; the luxury and corruption among the upper classes; moral degeneracy followed intellectual degeneration; its brothels, its opium parlors, its depravity; Rome had fallen into moral putrefaction
Synonyms: degeneracy, depravation, verb, social, deprave, depravity, adj, all, corrupt, depraved, putrefaction, immorality, moral, perversion, impairment, of, virtue, and, principles, the, luxury, among, upper, classes, followed, intellectual, degeneration, its, brothels, opium, parlors, Rome, had, fallen, into
Category: noun.attribute
